## Stack

React 19, TypeScript, Vite, Tailwind v4, shadcn/ui, **TanStack Query**, **Zustand**, react-hook-form + zod, `@microsoft/signalr`, lightweight-charts.

## Package manager (Yarn)

- **`web/` uses Yarn only** — lockfile is `yarn.lock`. Do not run `npm install` or commit `package-lock.json`.
- Prefer commands from repo root: `yarn --cwd web install`, `yarn --cwd web dev`, `yarn --cwd web build`, `yarn --cwd web lint`.
- shadcn: `yarn --cwd web dlx shadcn@latest add <component>` (or `yarn --cwd web exec shadcn add <component>`).
- Aspire AppHost: `AddViteApp("web", ...).WithYarn(...)` on the `web` resource (Aspire 13.3+).

## API access

- Frontends call **Api directly** (no BFF in MVP) — cookie session, `credentials: 'include'`
- Base URL from Vite env (`VITE_*` injected by Aspire)
- Centralize HTTP in `web/src/lib/` — feature code does not hardcode URLs

## Server state (TanStack Query)

```tsx
const walletQuery = useQuery({
  queryKey: ['wallet', userId],
  queryFn: ({ signal }) => api.wallet.get({ signal }),
  staleTime: 0,
});
```

- All REST reads/writes through Query mutations
- Mutations: optimistic update + rollback on error where safe
- SignalR pushes → `queryClient.setQueryData` or invalidate keys — avoid manual refetch storms

## Client state (Zustand)

- UI-only: chart interval, panel layout, form drafts
- **Never** duplicate server state (wallet, orders, portfolio) in Zustand

## Folder structure

```
web/src/
  app/           providers, router
  features/      auth | trading | portfolio | orders
  components/    shared + ui/ (shadcn)
  lib/           api client, signalr, utils
  store/         zustand
  types/         zod schemas
```

One feature = one folder. Cross-feature imports via `components/` or `lib/` only.

## Forms

react-hook-form + zod in `types/` — same schema for inference and validation. Mirror API rules (limit price required when type = limit, positive integer quantity).

## Real-time

- One SignalR connection per session (context/hook); auto-reconnect
- Groups: `market:{symbol}`, `user:{userId}` — see `api-guidelines.mdc`

## Testing

No automated frontend tests for MVP unless explicitly requested.

## DON'TS

- ❌ No `useEffect` for data fetching — use TanStack Query
- ❌ No hex colors in JSX — Tailwind semantic tokens (`bg-primary`, `text-muted-foreground`)
- ❌ No `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` for API-sourced strings
- ❌ No global mutable singletons outside Zustand/React context
